Artificial intelligence (AI) is here and evolving quickly. This webinar offers a unique opportunity to delve into the opportunities, promises, and challenges of AI in healthcare. Hosted by Schwartz Center Chief Medical Officer Beth Lown, MD, and moderated by yours truly, we'll explore how AI is reshaping the landscape of healthcare today and what we can expect in the future. Panelists: - Dr. Michael D. Lesh, SM MD FACC, CEO and founder of Quench - Dr. Ashwin Nayak, Clinical Assistant Professor of Medicine at Stanford University - Dr. Vivek Rudrapatna, Gastroenterologist and Assistant Professor at UCSF Together, we will discuss how AI impacts compassionate patient care and healthcare workforce well-being, and what steps we can take to shape this future positively.
